WEBVTT

00:02.830 --> 00:03.580
Previously on
"Grey's Anatomy"...

00:03.580 --> 00:04.330
Richard: Oh, uh --

00:04.330 --> 00:06.500
Um...sorry.

00:08.460 --> 00:10.120
Mom!
What are you doing here?

00:10.120 --> 00:11.620
What's going on?
Are you okay?

00:11.620 --> 00:13.330
Just a little consult.

00:13.330 --> 00:14.620
Breast cancer?

00:14.620 --> 00:16.000
I'm so sorry.

00:16.000 --> 00:17.420
Would you like me
to grab Maggie for you?

00:17.420 --> 00:19.420
Oh, no.
[ Sighs ]

00:19.420 --> 00:20.960
I had a baby.
Had?

00:20.960 --> 00:23.960
He lived for 43 minutes
without a brain.

00:23.960 --> 00:25.500
[ Voice breaking ]
And it almost killed me.

00:25.500 --> 00:26.880
...tell you
not to come home?
I cannot
keep doing this.

00:26.880 --> 00:28.330
Doing what?
I'm not --
I don't want
to have a baby!

00:29.830 --> 00:31.790
I think about you a lot,

00:31.790 --> 00:33.880
and I'm telling you,
I am in...

00:33.880 --> 00:35.330
if you are.

00:35.330 --> 00:36.580
What do you think?

00:39.960 --> 00:42.000
[ Earl St. Clair's
"Can't Stop" plays ]

00:42.000 --> 00:43.880
Man: Keep it moving, folks.
Come on.

00:43.880 --> 00:46.250
Move along, please.

00:46.250 --> 00:48.040
♪ I kinda had it tough
as a kid... ♪

00:48.040 --> 00:50.620
So, he says to me
that when I figure it out,

00:50.620 --> 00:51.920
I should give him a call.

00:51.920 --> 00:54.290
I mean, who says that?

00:54.290 --> 00:56.710
[ Cellphone buzzing ]
She found her mom
in baggage claim.

00:56.710 --> 00:59.420
Anyway,
he's an arrogant ass.

00:59.420 --> 01:01.670
And Maggie has terrible taste
in men.

01:01.670 --> 01:03.620
I don't like the guy.

01:03.620 --> 01:05.170
I mean,
the sex is great.

01:05.170 --> 01:07.250
Maybe I shouldn't be picky
about great sex.

01:07.250 --> 01:09.620
You should be picky about sex.
You're hot.

01:09.620 --> 01:11.290
Well, you have to say that
because I let you

01:11.290 --> 01:12.670
eat my food
and live in my house.

01:12.670 --> 01:13.670
Yes, but it's still true.

01:13.670 --> 01:15.000
Thank you.

01:15.000 --> 01:16.500
♪ The world don't care that much
'bout your hard work ♪

01:16.500 --> 01:17.750
There she is.

01:17.750 --> 01:19.250
Meredith: Stuff comes apart.

01:19.250 --> 01:22.080
An eggshell is never gonna come
back together.

01:22.080 --> 01:24.250
A window will never unbreak.

01:24.250 --> 01:26.500
30 seconds in,
she's talking about her boobs.

01:26.500 --> 01:29.120
That's what's on her mind --
her boob job, her boobs,

01:29.120 --> 01:31.580
which are perfectly fine,
by the way.

01:31.580 --> 01:32.540
You know what?

01:32.540 --> 01:33.790
When she gets in the car,
you look at them,

01:33.790 --> 01:34.920
and you tell me
that they're not perfect.

01:34.920 --> 01:36.880
I'm not gonna check out
your mom's boobs.

01:36.880 --> 01:39.710
It's called the
Second Law of Thermodynamics.

01:39.710 --> 01:41.120
It's also called life.

01:41.120 --> 01:43.460
♪ I won't stop ♪

01:43.460 --> 01:46.540
Oh, it's good to see you,
Meredith.

01:46.540 --> 01:49.500
Hi.
It's good to see you.
And, um, Alex, right?

01:49.500 --> 01:52.500
♪ 'Cause every obstacle
I seem to beat ♪

01:52.500 --> 01:54.670
♪ Can't stop, I won't stop ♪

01:54.670 --> 01:56.710
What did you tell them?

01:56.710 --> 01:58.330
What?!

01:58.330 --> 02:00.710
I'm not the one
getting the ginormous boobs!

02:00.710 --> 02:02.500
Stuff rarely comes together.

02:02.500 --> 02:04.420
[ Sighs ]

02:04.420 --> 02:06.380
But it'll always come apart.

02:06.380 --> 02:09.500
♪♪

02:09.500 --> 02:11.080
Arizona: Wait. You're saying
that you don't have the budget

02:11.080 --> 02:13.290
for dozens of babies and
their tiny beating baby hearts?

02:13.290 --> 02:14.580
Don't. Unh-unh. No.

02:14.580 --> 02:16.420
Every time you want something,
you say,

02:16.420 --> 02:18.250
"But the tiny babies.
The teeny, tiny babies."

02:18.250 --> 02:21.040
But you are the doctor
who cried, "Tiny baby."

02:21.040 --> 02:23.210
[ Stammers ]
Dr. Webber, you tell her.

02:23.210 --> 02:25.380
Robbins wants new
wireless fetal monitors,

02:25.380 --> 02:26.960
when the ones we have are --
It's not my concern.

02:29.750 --> 02:31.500
Well, damn.

02:31.500 --> 02:33.670
It's not you, it's me.
I pissed him off, too.

02:33.670 --> 02:35.000
Not like I did.

02:35.000 --> 02:36.710
Yeah,
a little bit like you did.

02:36.710 --> 02:38.330
What did you do?

02:38.330 --> 02:40.420
I have a patient.

02:40.420 --> 02:42.620
D--

02:42.620 --> 02:44.670
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

02:44.670 --> 02:47.290
Hello.
Incoming!

02:47.290 --> 02:48.620
DeLuca! Incoming.

02:50.620 --> 02:54.040
[ Siren wailing ]

02:54.040 --> 02:56.080
ETA less than a minute.

02:56.080 --> 02:58.710
I didn't know
you were back.

02:58.710 --> 03:00.750
They said
one of the patients had syncope.

03:00.750 --> 03:02.330
You'll need
a neuro consult.

03:02.330 --> 03:04.040
I just meant,
how are you doing?

03:04.040 --> 03:05.830
[ Siren wails ]

03:08.380 --> 03:09.790
It's nice to be working.

03:09.790 --> 03:12.120
But it's, uh --
But it's gonna be a busy day.

03:12.120 --> 03:13.790
I'm hoping this will be
quick and easy.

03:13.790 --> 03:15.420
[ Ambulance doors opening ]

03:17.120 --> 03:19.960
Elsie Clatch, 95,
fainted while hiking,

03:19.960 --> 03:23.670
but now G.C.S. is 15,
vitals are stable.

03:23.670 --> 03:26.000
Gently, gently.
She's been injured.

03:26.000 --> 03:28.380
Please, Lewis,
all this fuss.

03:28.380 --> 03:31.330
Hiking?
How do you think I made it
to 95?

03:31.330 --> 03:33.170
Alert and oriented
times three.

03:33.170 --> 03:34.670
Sir,
did you injure your wrist?

03:34.670 --> 03:36.330
Uh, no, it's fine.

03:36.330 --> 03:39.750
He fell, too.
He wouldn't let go of my hand.

03:39.750 --> 03:41.500
No reason to take a chance, sir.
Let's go.

03:41.500 --> 03:44.460
[ Radio chatter ]

03:44.460 --> 03:48.120
Her syncopal episode lasted
at least 60 seconds.

03:48.120 --> 03:49.580
Oh, it sounds like
you've been watching a lot

03:49.580 --> 03:50.960
of medical shows, sir.

03:50.960 --> 03:52.920
Elsie:
He's not gonna like that.

03:52.920 --> 03:54.830
I'm a
cardiothoracic surgeon.

03:55.790 --> 03:57.710
Owen: 1, 2, 3.

03:57.710 --> 03:58.960
[ All grunting ]

03:58.960 --> 04:01.210
Elsie: Don't be pompous.

04:01.210 --> 04:04.080
You were a surgeon.
So was I.

04:04.080 --> 04:05.790
They're surgeons now.

04:05.790 --> 04:08.040
She'll need a head C.T.

04:08.040 --> 04:10.290
Still, we'd like to rule out
other injuries.

04:10.290 --> 04:11.330
Oh, It's nothing.

04:11.330 --> 04:13.170
I-I just got
a little lightheaded.

04:13.170 --> 04:14.670
You don't know
it's nothing.

04:14.670 --> 04:16.710
I know as much as you do.

04:17.830 --> 04:19.710
I fell down.

04:19.710 --> 04:22.670
I'm old. I'm allowed.

04:22.670 --> 04:26.500
You'll need an EKG
and labs with cardiac enzymes.

04:33.670 --> 04:35.080
You heard the man.

04:39.710 --> 04:43.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:43.170 --> 04:44.460
Hey.

04:44.460 --> 04:46.250
Hi.

04:46.250 --> 04:48.210
Pierce asked if she could
discharge the triple-A

04:48.210 --> 04:49.500
that you guys
were working on

04:49.500 --> 04:51.330
if you didn't have
any objections.

04:51.330 --> 04:53.330
Nope, not at all.

04:53.330 --> 04:54.540
Great.

04:58.210 --> 05:01.250
So, did you have a chance
to think about it?

05:01.250 --> 05:03.540
Oh, no.
I don't need to think about it.

05:03.540 --> 05:05.040
You can discharge him.
No, no, no.

05:05.040 --> 05:06.880
I mean, uh,
the thing that I said

05:06.880 --> 05:08.830
about how I think
about you.

05:08.830 --> 05:10.620
No, I haven't
thought about it.

05:10.620 --> 05:13.250
I-I-I --
I have three kids...

05:13.250 --> 05:14.420
and a job.

05:14.420 --> 05:15.380
I'm a surgeon.

05:15.380 --> 05:16.580
Right.

05:20.330 --> 05:21.580
Take your time.

05:28.330 --> 05:29.920
How are you feeling?

05:29.920 --> 05:32.460
I'm -- I'm good.
Just a little tired.

05:32.460 --> 05:34.080
Yeah.

05:34.080 --> 05:37.580
Chemo's not my idea
of a great time.

05:37.580 --> 05:38.880
Sure.

05:38.880 --> 05:40.500
Well,
I spoke with your oncologist.

05:40.500 --> 05:43.380
She gave me a full report,
and the chemo's been working.

05:43.380 --> 05:46.380
Your repeat scans came back,
and they show a good response.

05:46.380 --> 05:47.880
You are her star patient.

05:47.880 --> 05:51.540
Ooh, and the prize is
a mastectomy.

05:51.540 --> 05:54.460
Your reconstruction
is gonna go perfectly.
It'll be my best work.

05:54.460 --> 05:56.920
Today, we just focus on getting
your pre-op taking care of,

05:56.920 --> 05:58.960
and we get our oncologist
up to speed.

05:58.960 --> 06:01.620
[ Keyboard keys clacking ]

06:01.620 --> 06:04.420
Did you want, um...
Maggie here before we continue?

06:07.960 --> 06:10.420
Um...
Diane,
you didn't tell her yet?

06:10.420 --> 06:12.790
It's too much stress.

06:12.790 --> 06:14.290
Which is exactly why
she needs to know,

06:14.290 --> 06:16.120
because it's gonna be
stressful enough for you.

06:16.120 --> 06:18.040
We're already fighting today.

06:18.040 --> 06:20.170
No, as your doctor,
I can't, in good confidence,

06:20.170 --> 06:21.460
continue to let this go on,
all right?

06:21.460 --> 06:23.790
It's bad for you both.
It's bad for everyone.

06:23.790 --> 06:25.710
Well, just not yet.

06:25.710 --> 06:27.960
When?
Our surgery is tomorrow.

06:27.960 --> 06:30.120
After.

06:30.120 --> 06:33.920
I can just have the surgery
and tell her then,

06:33.920 --> 06:37.750
and I can tell her
that I had cancer

06:37.750 --> 06:39.750
and not that I have it.

06:39.750 --> 06:42.670
That's not the best idea.

06:42.670 --> 06:44.500
It's how I want to do it.

06:47.120 --> 06:49.040
Is that understood?

06:49.040 --> 06:51.460
♪♪

07:10.170 --> 07:12.210
So, did Dr. Avery answer
all your questions?

07:12.210 --> 07:13.670
He sure did.

07:13.670 --> 07:15.920
So you discussed
everything?

07:15.920 --> 07:17.120
Even size?

07:17.120 --> 07:21.290
We discussed everything
I needed to discuss.

07:21.290 --> 07:23.040
So what did you decide,
size-wise?

07:23.040 --> 07:24.750
I just want to be prepared,
you know?

07:24.750 --> 07:26.540
I've been hugging
the same person

07:26.540 --> 07:28.120
for the last 30 years,
you know?

07:28.120 --> 07:29.750
This is a big --
Maggie.

07:29.750 --> 07:32.170
This is a big renovation.
Maggie.

07:32.170 --> 07:34.380
I-I don't want
to discuss this with you.

07:36.250 --> 07:38.210
Just...leave it alone.

07:38.210 --> 07:40.250
Fine.

07:40.250 --> 07:44.830
Well, I hope you'll enjoy being
a nice, self-involved,

07:44.830 --> 07:48.120
lonely person
with an incredible rack.

07:53.670 --> 07:55.170
Pretty straightforward
modified rad.

07:55.170 --> 07:57.830
I'll remove the breast tissue,
then do a lymph node dissection,

07:57.830 --> 07:59.580
and leave you
to the reconstruction.

07:59.580 --> 08:01.170
Sounds great.

08:02.750 --> 08:04.000
Need something?

08:04.000 --> 08:06.000
Yeah,
I'm on your service today.

08:06.000 --> 08:08.830
No, you're not.
I didn't request a resident.

08:08.830 --> 08:11.540
Dr. Minnick
assigned me to you.

08:11.540 --> 08:13.210
All right, I will, um...

08:13.210 --> 08:14.790
I'll talk to Dr. Minnick
after I finish up here,

08:14.790 --> 08:17.620
but no, thanks.
I don't need anyone.

08:17.620 --> 08:19.000
Okay, sorry.
You all set?

08:19.000 --> 08:20.830
Yeah,
I'll see you tomorrow.

08:20.830 --> 08:22.040
Thanks very much.

08:24.710 --> 08:27.000
This is Diane Pierce?

08:27.000 --> 08:28.580
No, no, no. Do not look at that.
You're not on this case.

08:28.580 --> 08:30.620
Is this Maggie's mother?

08:30.620 --> 08:32.250
Wilson, please.
Maggie: Jackson!

08:32.250 --> 08:34.120
Hey.

08:34.120 --> 08:35.750
What the hell?

08:35.750 --> 08:37.120
Why am I locked out
of my mother's file?

08:37.120 --> 08:38.620
I'm a doctor.

08:38.620 --> 08:40.380
Yes, well,
she requested privacy.

08:40.380 --> 08:42.920
I'm her daughter.

08:42.920 --> 08:44.420
She can't handle the fact
that I might have an opinion

08:44.420 --> 08:45.830
about her boob job.

08:45.830 --> 08:47.710
She's anxious because
she's going into surgery.

08:47.710 --> 08:49.710
Now you're telling me
how my mom feels, Jackson?

08:49.710 --> 08:53.500
What is going on here?
Level with me.

08:53.500 --> 08:56.670
You saw what happened
the last time she was here.

08:56.670 --> 08:58.710
And I thought
we could actually fix it.

08:58.710 --> 09:00.290
I wanted to talk
and actually try,

09:00.290 --> 09:02.000
but she has been shutting me out
from moment one.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.670
Why is she doing this?

09:05.670 --> 09:07.710
You know, I really --
I really couldn't say.

09:07.710 --> 09:09.920
Is she embarrassed
about the boob job?

09:09.920 --> 09:10.960
Then why is she getting it?

09:10.960 --> 09:13.540
She's scared...
about her surgery.

09:13.540 --> 09:16.500
I mean, she needs support.
She needs your support.

09:16.500 --> 09:18.710
So I'm awful,
is what you're saying.

09:18.710 --> 09:20.290
It's --
You know that's not what I mean.

09:20.290 --> 09:23.540
Okay. I'll try.

09:23.540 --> 09:26.290
I will leave it alone.
I will try.

09:26.290 --> 09:28.790
Thank you.

09:28.790 --> 09:30.460
Just tell me,
are they gonna be huge-huge?

09:30.460 --> 09:31.920
Maggie, please.
Just trust me.

09:31.920 --> 09:34.170
♪♪

09:34.170 --> 09:35.880
Okay, thank you.

09:35.880 --> 09:37.620
Wow.

09:37.620 --> 09:38.750
No, no, no. Don't.

09:38.750 --> 09:40.380
I don't need to remind you
of HIPAA, right?

09:40.380 --> 09:43.040
Okay,
nothing to be discussed.

09:43.040 --> 09:45.120
Right. Sorry.

09:45.120 --> 09:48.670
Well, you know now.
So I guess I can use you.

09:48.670 --> 09:50.830
Only if you can --
I-I can.

09:50.830 --> 09:54.330
All right.
Then go ahead. Get prepped.

09:54.330 --> 09:55.960
Close the door, please.

10:03.330 --> 10:04.880
[ Sighs ]

10:04.880 --> 10:07.710
Elsie: We do this hike
every other day.

10:07.710 --> 10:10.750
I don't know
why today I got so wonky.

10:10.750 --> 10:13.330
Squeeze my fingers, Elsie?
Hard as you can?

10:15.210 --> 10:16.960
Very good.
I'm sorry.

10:16.960 --> 10:19.540
Are you the Dr. Clatch?

10:19.540 --> 10:21.170
Uh...

10:21.170 --> 10:23.420
I'm one of two,
yeah.

10:23.420 --> 10:24.580
You -- You are.

10:27.580 --> 10:30.620
Uh-huh.
You worked with Dr. Raven.

10:30.620 --> 10:33.080
Uh, geez,
don't remind me.

10:33.080 --> 10:35.830
You helped develop the
cardiopulmonary bypass machine.

10:35.830 --> 10:39.420
The man was
a blowhard and a grabass.

10:39.420 --> 10:41.500
That is true.
Right.

10:41.500 --> 10:44.120
So, were you there
when he first connected a child

10:44.120 --> 10:45.500
to his mother's
circulation?

10:45.500 --> 10:46.880
Okay,
let's all focus, please.

10:46.880 --> 10:49.580
Was I there?
Yeah.

10:49.580 --> 10:51.580
I did most of it.

10:53.080 --> 10:55.420
[ Chuckles ]

10:55.420 --> 10:58.960
DeLuca, take her to C.T.
and page me when she's done.
All right.

10:58.960 --> 11:01.790
Dr. Clatch,
I'll be happy to show you

11:01.790 --> 11:03.880
where you can wait, okay?

11:03.880 --> 11:06.460
No, you will not.
I'm gonna stay with my wife.

11:06.460 --> 11:09.000
Oh, stop.
You don't know brains.

11:09.000 --> 11:10.250
I know enough!

11:11.670 --> 11:14.290
Dr. Clatch?
Okay, follow me.

11:14.290 --> 11:15.580
Huh? Yeah.

11:24.920 --> 11:26.540
Would you page me when
her studies are back, please?

11:35.670 --> 11:37.000
Hey.

11:37.000 --> 11:38.920
Just stop it.

11:38.920 --> 11:39.920
Stop what?

11:39.920 --> 11:41.170
Pretending
like we're doctors.

11:41.170 --> 11:42.120
We are doctors.

11:42.120 --> 11:43.500
I'm your husband!

11:43.500 --> 11:45.210
You can't hide
in plain sight from me

11:45.210 --> 11:47.290
and...ignore the fact
that we haven't talked,

11:47.290 --> 11:48.830
and that we have things --
I'm at work. We are working.

11:48.830 --> 11:51.080
You're trying to act
like nothing happened!

11:51.080 --> 11:52.830
You ran out on me.

11:52.830 --> 11:55.040
You ran away from home!

11:55.040 --> 11:56.080
From your husband.

11:56.080 --> 11:57.290
You're married.
We got married!

11:57.290 --> 11:59.500
I know!
We took vows...

11:59.500 --> 12:01.710
for better or for worse.

12:01.710 --> 12:04.380
Amelia, you [scoffs]

12:04.380 --> 12:07.420
running out, acting this way is
not how a marriage works.

12:07.420 --> 12:09.750
So I need you to tell me
right now.

12:09.750 --> 12:12.710
Are you ever coming home
so we can work this out...

12:12.710 --> 12:13.620
or not?

12:19.540 --> 12:21.710
[ Sighs ]

12:21.710 --> 12:22.500
Perfect.

12:26.460 --> 12:28.960
You need to decide
what you want.

12:28.960 --> 12:29.960
Because I know.

12:32.170 --> 12:34.420
I know what I want.

12:36.380 --> 12:37.710
And at some point...

12:37.710 --> 12:39.380
you need
to figure that out, too.

12:41.000 --> 12:42.250
Just pull it together.

12:55.710 --> 12:56.880
Stephanie: So,
you weren't into the idea

12:56.880 --> 12:58.750
of her being a surgeon
at first?

12:58.750 --> 13:01.290
I was.
Oh, he wasn't!

13:01.290 --> 13:02.380
[ Laughs ]

13:02.380 --> 13:04.880
I was halfway
through my residency,

13:04.880 --> 13:06.330
and Lewis said to me,

13:06.330 --> 13:08.750
"Elsie,
this surgeon business

13:08.750 --> 13:11.250
is not making you
any friends.

13:11.250 --> 13:14.460
You need to think
of something else to do."

13:14.460 --> 13:16.880
I was trying
to take care of you!

13:16.880 --> 13:18.670
But you didn't, did you?

13:18.670 --> 13:20.170
I did not.

13:20.170 --> 13:21.750
Good.
Because you knew
what you wanted.

13:21.750 --> 13:24.170
Oh!
This one gets it.

13:24.170 --> 13:26.880
Well, it was
a different time back then.

13:26.880 --> 13:29.290
It was. It was.

13:29.290 --> 13:32.330
All right, let's give
the Clatches some air.

13:32.330 --> 13:33.920
They are not here
for your entertainment, guys.

13:33.920 --> 13:35.420
Time to go.

13:35.420 --> 13:37.880
Oh, let them stay.
How else they gonna learn?

13:37.880 --> 13:39.420
They have
a lot of work to do.

13:39.420 --> 13:41.920
This is a teaching hospital,
right?

13:41.920 --> 13:43.710
So teach them.

13:43.710 --> 13:46.290
It's all right.
Come on back.

13:50.380 --> 13:54.080
