Why didn't you
just tell me?!

29:16.120 --> 29:20.420
I am your friend...
Maggie, but I'm also her doctor.

29:22.460 --> 29:23.960
Go fix her.

29:23.960 --> 29:26.080
♪♪

29:26.080 --> 29:28.750
[ Door opens ]

29:28.750 --> 29:31.330
[ Door closes ]

29:42.170 --> 29:43.920
I want two-hour neuro checks

29:43.920 --> 29:45.790
and call me immediately
for any signs of increased ICP.

29:45.790 --> 29:47.960
Got it.

29:47.960 --> 29:49.920
Nice job.

29:49.920 --> 29:51.540
Thanks.

29:51.540 --> 29:52.960
I know I was against it,

29:52.960 --> 29:54.380
but it looks like
you were right.

29:54.380 --> 29:57.960
I think you gave that couple
more time together.

29:57.960 --> 29:59.290
I don't care...

29:59.290 --> 30:00.920
what you think.

30:00.920 --> 30:02.330
Amelia, stop.

30:02.330 --> 30:05.250
You don't have any right
to an opinion.

30:05.250 --> 30:06.920
And you certainly don't have
the right to bully me.

30:06.920 --> 30:09.170
Bully you?

30:10.960 --> 30:13.750
You don't have the right
to give me ultimatums

30:13.750 --> 30:17.170
about when to come home
and make up my mind.
Okay.

30:17.170 --> 30:20.500
For better or for worse --
that's what you said.

30:20.500 --> 30:23.540
Well, guess what.
This is the "for worse"!

30:23.540 --> 30:25.460
And you don't have the right
to just decide

30:25.460 --> 30:27.210
that I don't have myself
together, okay?

30:27.210 --> 30:29.460
You -- You don't make me the one
who is wrong.

30:29.460 --> 30:31.880
I am tired of being
the messed-up one, okay,

30:31.880 --> 30:33.210
because I'm not.

30:33.210 --> 30:35.080
You are at least
as messed up as me.

30:35.080 --> 30:36.290
You disappeared!

30:36.290 --> 30:38.120
You are suffocating me!

30:39.250 --> 30:42.080
That is unfair.
Really?

30:42.080 --> 30:46.460
I would love to ask Christina
how suffocated she felt by you,

30:46.460 --> 30:48.620
by your needs,
by your idea of a baby,

30:48.620 --> 30:49.790
by what you want.

30:49.790 --> 30:52.620
All right! Stop!

30:52.620 --> 30:53.920
Not here.

30:59.960 --> 31:02.250
[ Door slams ]
I only wanted the same thing
you said you wanted.

31:02.250 --> 31:04.330
You told me --
Okay,
why do you even want a baby?

31:04.330 --> 31:05.670
Have you
asked yourself that?

31:05.670 --> 31:07.620
What? Why do I want a baby?
Yes, yes.

31:07.620 --> 31:09.580
What do you need
that you don't have

31:09.580 --> 31:11.290
that you think a baby
is going to bring you?

31:11.290 --> 31:13.540
I want a family.
You have one!

31:13.540 --> 31:15.580
You and me --
That makes one.

31:15.580 --> 31:17.790
What else?
W-W-What do you need?

31:17.790 --> 31:19.380
[ Sighs ]

31:19.380 --> 31:21.080
I mean,
it's normal to want --

31:21.080 --> 31:24.290
No, you don't get to call
what is normal!

31:24.290 --> 31:26.080
You don't know.

31:26.080 --> 31:28.210
You want a dream, Owen.

31:29.670 --> 31:32.500
And when you have
a child...

31:32.500 --> 31:34.960
you might not get to have
what you asked for.

31:34.960 --> 31:37.960
You get what you are given.

31:37.960 --> 31:41.500
And it might be wonderful.

31:41.500 --> 31:45.250
And it might be painful,
and it might be both.

31:45.250 --> 31:48.330
I know you're scared,
but...

31:48.330 --> 31:50.040
Amelia,
I think you'd be an amazing mom.

31:53.170 --> 31:55.460
I was already
an amazing mom, Owen.

31:55.460 --> 31:57.580
For better and for worse.

32:00.620 --> 32:01.670
Are you here for that?

32:04.120 --> 32:06.290
Are you here for that?

32:15.880 --> 32:17.210
Or do we just play
by your rules,

32:17.210 --> 32:20.080
by your "normal" rules?

32:20.920 --> 32:23.620
'Cause that's not life.

32:23.620 --> 32:26.250
It's not a marriage.

32:26.250 --> 32:28.170
Not one that's gonna last.

32:28.170 --> 32:30.540
[ Sleeping at Last's
"Anger" plays ]
[ Door opens ]

32:30.540 --> 32:34.170
♪ Like wildfire ♪
[ Door slams ]

32:38.330 --> 32:41.540
♪ It starts in my chest ♪

32:46.170 --> 32:51.080
♪ The silence grows louder ♪

32:54.210 --> 32:57.210
♪ Ringing out in my head ♪

33:03.960 --> 33:06.540
♪ But I feel it break ♪

33:06.540 --> 33:10.330
♪ With just one misstep
down the fire escape ♪

33:10.330 --> 33:14.120
♪ And suddenly,
I am someone that prays ♪

33:14.120 --> 33:17.000
♪ A last minute man of faith ♪

33:20.920 --> 33:22.210
♪ Alarms will sound ♪

33:22.210 --> 33:26.250
♪ But it's too late
for holy water now ♪

33:26.250 --> 33:30.210
♪ Sooner or later,
the fire dies down ♪

33:30.210 --> 33:33.420
♪ Then I'll open my eyes again ♪

34:01.620 --> 34:03.170
How we doing?
Feeling better?

34:03.170 --> 34:04.170
A little more --

34:07.500 --> 34:10.170
16:22.

34:10.460 --> 34:12.290
I'm sorry?

34:12.290 --> 34:15.620
16:22...

34:15.620 --> 34:18.040
the time of her death.

34:20.710 --> 34:23.380
For when you want
to put it down.

34:23.380 --> 34:25.580
I looked.

34:59.920 --> 35:01.920
[ Sighs ]

35:01.920 --> 35:03.960
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

35:03.960 --> 35:05.670
Okay, all right.
Got it.

35:12.080 --> 35:13.710
I think that we should talk
about what you saw

35:13.710 --> 35:15.920
with Eliza and I.

35:15.920 --> 35:17.750
Arizona...

35:17.750 --> 35:21.580
you've always had
an active love life.

35:21.580 --> 35:24.170
If I worried about
who you've been kissing on,

35:24.170 --> 35:26.420
it would leave me little time
for anything else.

35:26.420 --> 35:29.080
Okay, you're mad,
and you didn't mean that.

35:29.080 --> 35:31.750
Yes, I did.

35:31.750 --> 35:34.040
No, I didn't.

35:34.040 --> 35:36.040
Damn it.

35:36.040 --> 35:37.920
This is what
I've turned into.

35:37.920 --> 35:43.380
I've become this person who
takes sides and counts votes.

35:43.380 --> 35:46.040
It's ugly, and it's bitter,
and it's small.

35:46.040 --> 35:47.790
This is
what Bailey's done here.

35:47.790 --> 35:51.380
I'm -- I'm so sorry.

35:51.380 --> 35:54.580
You said you were with me,
Robbins.

35:54.580 --> 35:56.080
I believed you.
I was.

35:56.080 --> 35:57.620
I am.

35:57.620 --> 35:59.210
I j--

35:59.210 --> 36:01.080
I just didn't expect
to feel this way, okay?

36:01.080 --> 36:03.330
I-I-I didn't try to.

36:03.330 --> 36:06.380
Okay, you know what?
I need some time, okay?

36:06.380 --> 36:07.620
I'll...

36:07.620 --> 36:10.710
I'll come around, but...

36:10.710 --> 36:12.420
I need some damn time.

36:12.420 --> 36:14.250
Take all the time you need.

36:20.040 --> 36:22.380
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

36:24.960 --> 36:27.420
[ Sighs deeply ]

36:27.420 --> 36:31.000
Well, I can call the morgue,
and I can finish her paperwork.

36:32.880 --> 36:35.250
Hey.

36:35.250 --> 36:37.670
Hey, look, she was 95.

36:37.670 --> 36:38.960
Okay, you were right.

36:38.960 --> 36:40.210
They had way more time
than most.

36:40.210 --> 36:42.330
They wanted more.

36:42.330 --> 36:44.380
She wanted more.

36:44.380 --> 36:46.750
That was the only reason
to do the surgery.

36:49.170 --> 36:51.580
And we took away
what little time they had.

36:51.580 --> 36:54.960
Shepherd said her co-morbidities
made it unlikely that she'd --

36:54.960 --> 36:57.250
Why do we do it?

37:00.330 --> 37:02.960
Why do we do any of it?
Why --

37:02.960 --> 37:04.500
[ Voice breaking ]
If we can't do

37:04.500 --> 37:08.040
what we say we were gonna do,
then...

37:08.040 --> 37:11.460
If we actually have
no control,

37:11.460 --> 37:16.170
then how dare we tell them
we can, you know?

37:18.040 --> 37:20.710
It --

37:20.710 --> 37:22.080
I think
I'm in love with Jo.

37:26.460 --> 37:28.040
I m-might be.
I...

37:30.710 --> 37:33.000
I'm pretty sure.

37:33.000 --> 37:34.000
Stop talking.

37:34.000 --> 37:35.830
Stop talking.

37:35.830 --> 37:37.500
I want more.

37:37.500 --> 37:40.540
[ Breathing shakily ]

37:40.540 --> 37:41.790
Hey.
Go away.

37:41.790 --> 37:42.960
I'm sorry.
Go away.

37:45.710 --> 37:47.380
Hey.
No.

37:47.380 --> 37:50.210
[ Sniffles ]

37:50.210 --> 37:51.620
It's okay.

37:53.500 --> 37:55.750
[ Sobbing ]

37:55.750 --> 37:58.210
[ Inhales, exhales sharply ]

38:02.040 --> 38:05.670
Nathan:
I don't have a good reason.

38:05.670 --> 38:08.380
I tried to come up
with one.

38:08.380 --> 38:12.540
So then I thought,
"Well, why do I like her?"

38:12.540 --> 38:15.290
And I don't know.

38:15.290 --> 38:18.170
From the first time I saw you,
you were at the O.R. board.

38:18.170 --> 38:19.540
You were talking
with Pierce,

38:19.540 --> 38:20.580
and she said something
that made you laugh,

38:20.580 --> 38:23.620
and...I couldn't move.

38:25.830 --> 38:28.120
And then I had to wait for you
to write your name on the board

38:28.120 --> 38:31.170
because...I just needed to know
who you were.

38:31.170 --> 38:32.880
So, I d-- I don't have

38:32.880 --> 38:36.170
a good reason
for you to like me.

38:36.170 --> 38:39.170
I didn't even try to like you.
I didn't want to.

38:39.170 --> 38:40.500
And I certainly don't want

38:40.500 --> 38:42.170
to have to think about you
all the time,

38:42.170 --> 38:46.170
trying to come in early,
see your name on the board,

38:46.170 --> 38:48.920
come up with that one thing
that's gonna make you smile

38:48.920 --> 38:51.790
so your eyes
do that thing they do.

38:51.790 --> 38:56.080
Anyway, uh...
so that's why I joke so much

38:56.080 --> 39:00.460
and to keep from having to say
anything like this.
[ Laughs ]

39:00.460 --> 39:03.460
So, I don't have
a good reason.

39:03.460 --> 39:05.330
I'm sorry.
I wish I did.

39:10.710 --> 39:13.250
[ Sighs ]

39:13.250 --> 39:15.420
Okay, so you should ask me
out to dinner.

39:19.170 --> 39:20.170
Do you want to go
out to dinner?

39:20.170 --> 39:21.790
Yes.

39:21.790 --> 39:24.880
[ Charlotte OC's
"Where It Stays" plays ]

39:24.880 --> 39:27.210
Dr. Grey,
Dr. Pierce needs you.

39:27.210 --> 39:28.670
Okay. Sorry.

39:28.670 --> 39:32.000
♪ I never knew I would cry
when I heard your name ♪

39:34.920 --> 39:36.880
Owen:
So, another signature here.

39:36.880 --> 39:39.040
♪ And now I'm running to your
heart 'cause I feel the pain ♪

39:39.040 --> 39:42.460
Um...
Do you know what funeral home
you want yet?

39:42.460 --> 39:44.290
No,
o-our church might know.

39:44.290 --> 39:46.040
♪ We found the devil
in our love ♪

39:46.040 --> 39:48.170
Do I have
to fill all this out now?

39:48.170 --> 39:50.380
Can I do this
in the morning?

39:50.380 --> 39:52.250
Of course you can.

39:52.250 --> 39:55.080
Everything can wait
until tomorrow.
Okay.

39:55.080 --> 39:57.120
Is there anything else
I can do for you?

39:57.120 --> 40:00.040
Well...
I-I don't have a car.

40:00.040 --> 40:03.330
Elsie and I
came in an ambulance.

40:03.330 --> 40:05.420
Well,
let me call you a cab.

40:05.420 --> 40:07.540
No, it's -- it's fine.

40:07.540 --> 40:11.250
Just...tell me
where I can get one.

40:11.250 --> 40:13.250
I'm --
I'm all turned around.

40:13.250 --> 40:17.290
Well, just go out here,
turn right, and at the corner.

40:17.290 --> 40:19.880
But, Dr. Clatch,
please, let me just get you a --

40:19.880 --> 40:21.920
No, I...

40:21.920 --> 40:25.290
I have to figure things out
for myself now.

40:25.290 --> 40:27.960
I-I -- Okay.

40:27.960 --> 40:28.750
Thank you.

40:28.750 --> 40:31.620
Here.
That's for you.

40:31.620 --> 40:33.120
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you.

40:33.120 --> 40:36.580
♪ It makes me really angry
when you can't relate ♪

40:39.290 --> 40:44.670
♪ Makes me feel like
you're living when I'm away ♪

40:46.000 --> 40:48.290
♪ So tell me
where you heart is ♪

40:48.290 --> 40:50.290
♪ Tell me where you keep it ♪

40:50.290 --> 40:54.380
♪ Tell me where it stays ♪

40:54.380 --> 40:56.380
♪ Tell me where your heart is ♪

40:56.380 --> 40:58.380
♪ Tell me where you keep it ♪

40:58.380 --> 41:02.540
♪ Tell me where it stays ♪

41:02.540 --> 41:04.540
♪ Tell me where your heart is ♪

41:04.540 --> 41:06.540
♪ Tell me where you keep it ♪
[ Elevator bell dings ]

41:06.540 --> 41:08.920
Meredith: Everything comes apart
at some point.

41:08.920 --> 41:10.920
We all will.
It's the law.

41:10.920 --> 41:12.880
♪ Tell me where your heart is ♪

41:12.880 --> 41:14.620
It's what we were designed
to do.

41:14.620 --> 41:18.580
♪ Tell me where it stays ♪

41:18.580 --> 41:20.580
♪ Tell me where your heart is ♪

41:20.580 --> 41:22.580
♪ Tell me where you keep it ♪

41:22.580 --> 41:26.750
♪ Tell me where it stays ♪

41:26.750 --> 41:28.790
♪ Tell me where your heart is ♪

41:28.790 --> 41:30.250
♪ Tell me where you keep it ♪

41:30.250 --> 41:32.960
[ Voice breaking ]
My mom is really sick.

41:32.960 --> 41:37.790
We have to face it
and accept it...

41:37.790 --> 41:40.000
[ Vocalizing ]

41:47.040 --> 41:50.420
...and try
to hold it together...

41:50.420 --> 41:53.960
♪ When we're not together,
I'm so afraid ♪

41:57.040 --> 41:58.380
...for as long as we can.

41:58.380 --> 42:01.670
♪ When we're not together,
I'm so afraid ♪

42:17.080 --> 42:19.960
♪♪
